description: Enforce the real app stack only
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json,sql,yml,yaml,md,mdc}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

This project must follow the actual app stack only.

Approved infrastructure and services:
- Hetzner
- Coolify
- Bunny Storage
- LiveKit
- Neon

Use only technologies already present in the repository and required by the current feature.

Strictly forbidden unless explicitly requested:
- do not introduce Supabase
- do not introduce Apwrite
- do not introduce DigitalOcean
- do not introduce Ghost
- do not introduce Netlify
- do not introduce Railway
- do not introduce Firebase
- do not introduce Vercel-specific architecture unless already present
- do not introduce WebRTC directly unless required by LiveKit integration
- do not migrate backend, storage, database, deployment, or live systems to another provider
- do not suggest replacing current infrastructure with unrelated alternatives
- do not generate code that assumes forbidden services are installed

Backend and infra rules:
- preserve existing Hetzner deployment assumptions
- preserve Coolify deployment flow
- preserve Bunny Storage usage for media/assets if already present
- preserve LiveKit flow for live/video features
- preserve Neon database usage and existing query patterns
- do not invent third-party serverless platform flows for unused services

Code generation rules:
- prefer the existing project structure
- prefer existing libraries already installed
- do not add new dependencies unless clearly necessary
- do not rewrite working code to match another stack
- do not fabricate env vars for services that are not used

Default behavior:
follow the real stack only and do not introduce unused platforms.
